					<li>(0.58,0.05)</li>
				</offsets>
			</li>
		</modExtensions>
		<generateCommonality>0.05</generateCommonality> <!-- Uncommon -->
		<comps>
			<li Class="MVCF.Comps.CompProperties_VerbProps">
				<compClass>MVCF.Comps.Comp_VerbProps</compClass>
				<verbProps>
					<li>
						<label>M4A1</label>
						<canBeToggled>true</canBeToggled>
						<separateToggle>false</separateToggle>
					</li>
					<li>
						<label>KAC Masterkey</label>
						<canBeToggled>true</canBeToggled>
						<separateToggle>false</separateToggle>
						<description>Caliber: 12 Gauge. 3-round tube. Single shot.					
The Knight's Armament Company (KAC) Masterkey is a cut down Remington 870 shotgun built to attach to the barrel/rail of an M16 or M4 rifle. Primarily designed for breaching doors, the Masterkey was created to replace the need for US infantrymen to carry a separate shotgun used in the same task. Used for many years on an unofficial basis, the Masterkey ultimately lost out to the C-More M26 MASS shotgun and was never adopted, but remains a fairly iconic attachment for the M16 series.</description>
					</li>
				</verbProps>
			</li>
		</comps>
